proceeded
to
make
the
selection.
She
looked
and
looked,
longing
to
know
which
might
be
least
valuable;
and
was
determined
in
her
choice
at
last,
by
fancying
there
was
one
necklace
more
frequently
placed
before
her
eyes
than
the
rest.
It
was
of
gold,
prettily
worked;
and
though
Fanny
would
have
preferred
a
longer
and
a
plainer
chain
as
