was
wrong;
"you
are
quite
mistaken.
How
could
Mr.
Crawford
say
such
a
thing?
I
gave
him
no
encouragement
yesterday.
On
the
contrary,
I
told
him,
I
cannot
recollect
my
exact
words,
but
I
am
sure
I
told
him
that
I
would
not
listen
to
him,
that
it
was
very
unpleasant
to
me
in
every
respect,
and
that
I
begged
him
never
to
talk
to
me
in
that
