again.
I
am
sure
I
said
as
much
as
that
and
more;
and
I
should
have
said
still
more,
if
I
had
been
quite
certain
of
his
meaning
anything
seriously;
but
I
did
not
like
to
be,
I
could
not
bear
to
be,
imputing
more
than
might
be
intended.
I
thought
it
might
all
pass
for
nothing
with
him."
She
could
say
no
more;
her
