situation
in
life,
fortune,
and
character,
but
with
more
than
common
agreeableness,
with
address
and
conversation
pleasing
to
everybody.
And
he
is
not
an
acquaintance
of
to
day;
you
have
now
known
him
some
time.
His
sister,
moreover,
is
your
intimate
friend,
and
he
has
been
doing
that
for
your
brother,
which
I
should
suppose
would
have
been
almost
sufficient
