after
such
a
picture
as
her
uncle
had
drawn,
for
not
liking
Mr.
Crawford.
"You
must
have
been
aware,"
continued
Sir
Thomas
presently,
"you
must
have
been
some
time
aware
of
a
particularity
in
Mr.
Crawford's
manners
to
you.
This
cannot
have
