I
never
perceived
them
to
be
unpleasant
to
you.
I
am
half
inclined
to
think,
Fanny,
that
you
do
not
quite
know
your
own
feelings."
"Oh
yes,
sir!
indeed
I
do.
His
attentions
were
always
what
I
did
not
like."
Sir
Thomas
looked
at
