On
the
morrow
the
Crawfords
were
gone.
Mr.
Crawford
gone,
Sir
Thomas's
next
object
was
that
he
should
be
missed;
and
he
entertained
great
hope
that
his
niece
would
find
a
blank
in
the
loss
of
those
attentions
which
at
the
time
she
had
felt,
or
