Alas!
it
was
this
sister,
this
friend
and
companion,
who
was
now
the
chief
bane
of
Fanny's
comfort.
If
she
could
have
believed
Mary's
future
fate
as
unconnected
with
Mansfield
as
she
was
determined
the
brother's
should
be,
if
she
could
have
hoped
her
return
thither
to
be
as
distant
as
