of
being
so;
darkened,
yet
fancying
itself
light.
She
might
love,
but
she
did
not
deserve
Edmund
by
any
other
sentiment.
Fanny
believed
there
was
scarcely
a
second
feeling
in
common
between
them;
and
she
may
be
forgiven
by
older
sages
for
looking
on
the
chance
of
Miss
Crawford's
future
