men
and
boys
at
last
all
in
motion
together,
the
moment
came
for
setting
off;
everything
was
ready,
William
took
leave,
and
all
of
them
were
gone;
for
the
three
boys,
in
spite
of
their
mother's
entreaty,
determined
to
see
their
brother
and
Mr.
Campbell
to
the
sally
port;
and
Mr.
Price
walked
off
at
the
same
time
to
carry
back
his
neighbour's
newspaper.
Something
like
tranquillity
might
now
be
hoped
for;
and
accordingly,
when
Rebecca
had
been
prevailed
on
to
carry
away
the
tea
things,
and
Mrs.
Price
had
walked
about
the
room
some
time
looking
for
a
shirt
