to
think
of
her
eldest
daughter
and
the
friends
she
had
come
from.
A
few
inquiries
began:
but
one
of
the
earliest
"How
did
sister
Bertram
manage
about
her
servants?"
"Was
she
as
much
plagued
as
herself
to
get
tolerable
servants?"
soon
led
her
mind
away
from
Northamptonshire,
and
fixed
it
on
her
own
domestic
grievances,
and
the
shocking
character
of
all
the
Portsmouth
