of
whom
she
believed
her
own
two
were
the
very
worst,
engrossed
her
completely.
The
Bertrams
were
all
forgotten
in
detailing
the
faults
of
Rebecca,
against
whom
Susan
had
also
much
to
depose,
and
little
Betsey
a
great
