now
sat
looking
at
Betsey,
she
could
not
but
think
particularly
of
another
sister,
a
very
pretty
little
girl,
whom
she
had
left
there
not
much
younger
when
she
went
into
Northamptonshire,
who
had
died
a
few
years
afterwards.
There
had
been
something
remarkably
amiable
about
her.
Fanny
in
those
