"now,
how
can
you
be
so
cross?
You
are
always
quarrelling
about
that
knife.
I
wish
you
would
not
be
so
quarrelsome.
Poor
little
Betsey;
how
cross
Susan
is
to
you!
But
you
should
not
have
taken
it
out,
my
dear,
when
I
sent
you
to
the
drawer.
You
know
I
told
you
not
to
touch
it,
because
Susan
is
so
cross
about
it.
I
must
hide
it
another
