of
going
to
bed;
and
before
Betsey
had
finished
her
cry
at
being
allowed
to
sit
up
only
one
hour
extraordinary
in
honour
of
sister,
she
was
off,
leaving
all
below
in
confusion
and
noise
again;
the
boys
begging
for
toasted
cheese,
her
father
calling
out
for
his
rum
and
