She
soon
learned
to
think
with
respect
of
her
own
little
attic
at
Mansfield
Park,
in
that
house
reckoned
too
small
for
anybody's
comfort.
Could
Sir
Thomas
have
seen
all
his
niece's
feelings,
when
she
wrote
her
first
letter
to
her
aunt,
he
would
not
have
despaired;
for
though
a
good
night's
rest,
a
pleasant
morning,
the
hope
of
soon
seeing
William
again,
and
the
