Time
did
something,
her
own
exertions
something
more,
and
she
resumed
her
attentions
to
Susan,
and
again
awakened
the
same
interest
in
them.
Susan
was
growing
very
fond
of
her,
and
though
without
any
of
the
early
delight
in
books
which
had
been
so
strong
in
Fanny,
with
a
disposition
much
less
inclined
to
sedentary
