Others
had
their
hour;
and
of
lesser
matters,
none
returned
so
often,
or
remained
so
long
between
them,
as
Mansfield
Park,
a
description
of
the
people,
the
manners,
the
amusements,
the
ways
of
Mansfield
Park.
Susan,
who
had
an
innate
taste
for
the
genteel
and
well
appointed,
was
eager
to
hear,
and
Fanny
could
not
but
indulge
herself
in
dwelling
on
so
beloved
