are
not
higher
than
her
own
fortune
may
warrant,
but
they
are
beyond
what
our
incomes
united
could
authorise.
There
is
comfort,
however,
even
here.
I
could
better
bear
to
lose
her
because
not
rich
enough,
than
because
of
my
profession.
That
would
only
prove
her
affection
not
equal
to
sacrifices,
which,
in
