ought,
by
going
down
to
Everingham
after
his
return
from
Portsmouth,
he
might
have
been
deciding
his
own
happy
destiny.
But
he
was
pressed
to
stay
for
Mrs.
Fraser's
party;
his
staying
was
made
of
flattering
consequence,
and
he
was
to
meet
Mrs.
Rushworth
there.
Curiosity
and
