resentment;
it
was
anger
on
Fanny's
account;
he
must
get
the
better
of
it,
and
make
Mrs.
Rushworth
Maria
Bertram
again
in
her
treatment
of
himself.
In
this
spirit
he
began
the
attack,
and
by
animated
perseverance
had
soon
re
established
the
sort
of
familiar
