was
long
in
finding
among
the
dashing
representatives,
or
idle
heir
apparents,
who
were
at
the
command
of
her
beauty,
and
her
20,000,
any
one
who
could
satisfy
the
better
taste
she
had
acquired
at
Mansfield,
whose
character
and
manners
could
authorise
a
hope
of
the
domestic
happiness
she
had
there
learned
to
estimate,
or
put
Edmund
Bertram
sufficiently
out
